      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Cycloheptatrienone is stable, but cyclopentadienone is so reactive that it can’t be isolated. Explain, taking the polarity of the carbonyl group into account.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBamtWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--5f2d58fd48a412d2ee09b320c7e5788f5cc5b410/OChem_15_EC_012.jpg\" alt=\"Cycloheptatrienone has a 7-carbon ring with three alternate double bonds. C 1 is carbonyl group. Cyclopentadienone has a 5-carbon ring with two alternate double bonds. C 1 is carbonyl group.\">",
